<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-10-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-10-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="932" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d932">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 892.001/4.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Siamese Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Siamese
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Gloucester,
                                    Mass.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-10-24"><hi rend="italic">October 24,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In deepest grief I beg to inform you that to the irreparable loss to my
                            country His Majesty the King of Siam, my august sovereign, passed away
                            yesterday morning at 12.45.</p>
                        <p>I also have the honor to announce to you that His Royal Highness the
                            Crown Prince has duly succeeded to the crown and has been proclaimed
                            King Maha Vajiravudh.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Akharaj
                            Varadhara.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>